5:
...So to sum it up, the Guild's been
scrambling to keep things together,
and the Farlands are also caught up
in the confusion.
8:
At the very least, we've managed to
convince everyone that nobody's
about to start any wars. The
situation's much better than what
happened with the Vesta.
16:
We decided it would be best to have
you help coordinate matters with
Shibuya.
18:
I'm sure you'll find this an agreeable
arrangement. You want to protect
both Shibuya and Palpebra, yes?
27:
Hey now, where's the energy? At
least try and turn some things to
your advantage, won't you?
29:
You're gonna need everything you
can get your hands on to keep
yourselves afloat. Seriously. You
can't be holding back in
negotiations like these.
39:
I, myself, have been taking
advantage of this situation to push
my reform plans ahead.
42:
See? Point is, you should rely on the
adults some more.
47:
I believe that is the right course as
well.
51:
...Does that mean we can ask you to
pick up after us?
56:
Whoa, hold on there, I didn't say to
use ME in particular... You're joking,
right?
64:
Come on, don't say that... Seriously,
don't. I've got enough on my plate
already.
80: Thank you for your aid, Zekhel.
84:
So your parents are doing fine now,
Yuki?
88:
Not just mine. The others are also
slowly waking up. I'm sure it won't be
long until your parents are up again.
91:
All those people that disappeared
when everything went down are
reappearing in the Kaleidoscope
too. Ain't that something?
94: I see... That's great to hear.
98:
Still, it's too bad that our powers got
weaker after coming here.
100: After I finally got stronger than you...
109:
Some of the Aegis kids were
unaffected though. There's
apparently a couple strong ones
causing trouble.
113:
Can't say that's surprising. They
were kings of the jungle for a while.
No way they're gonna turn over a
new leaf so fast.
116: That's pretty rich coming from you.
121:
I've decided that I'm going to help
out the Guild Knights, though the
Crimson Blades were also tempting.
124:
Speaking of which, Mr. Takamori's
been struggling to choose
something for himself.
128:
I'm gonna become a Kaleidoscope
adventurer. Figure I should help pull
out the others that show up in there.
133:
Guess that leaves me to help you
out, Yumu.
143:
What?! But I got my own powers
now too!
147:
Nuh-uh. No way. Be a good kid, and
focus on your studies.
152:
You're a kid too! And you also lost
super hard to other kids my age,
didn't you?!
161:
What are you gonna do anyway?
You seriously gonna pick a fight with
the gods of this place?
166: Once we're ready to go, at any rate.
169: I can't tell if you're brave or stupid...
176: Hope you weren't waiting too long.
180: I have a message from Nova.
182:
The Antipode Lance is charged up.
We are ready to go whenever.
186:
...So all that's left is to give the
go-ahead.
189: Yes. We'll win this no matter what.
201:
I just wanted to say thanks. Without
you, I don't think I could've gotten
this strong.
203:
Not that you can take ALL the credit,
but I definitely owe you.
207:
I've gotten stronger thanks to you
too.
221:
For now, we should gather everyone
for a nice dinner!
232:
This is the last we'll be seeing of this
place for a while. Are you ready?
